   "body" : "Doing some testing and seeing very slow reindex on my laptop:\r\n\r\n2016-06-22 09:51:04 Bitcoin version v0.12.99.0-9e45ef1-dirty\r\n2016-06-22 23:33:17 UpdateTip: new best=0000000000000000006becbd6a46552fb37225db2e34417352f04dc040f93652 height=328980 \r\n                 version=0x00000002 log2_work=81.374884 tx=50826071 date='2014-11-07 16:20:11' progress=0.377530 cache=51.0MiB(25600tx)\r\n\r\nThought it might be my machine but sipa tested and saw similar behavior.  Seems most time is going into flushing chainstate.  Not sure if it's a regression but it's very slow.\r\n\r\nOpening issue so we don't lost track of it before release.\r\n\r\n\r\n[Please tag for 0.13]",
